#pragma once

// kV4Hz — output frequency (Hz) of voice card V4 at every 12-bit DAC
// code 0..4095. V4 is the slope-best card from the all_voices set,
// gain-calibrated so DAC=1568 reads exactly 248.000 Hz (factor
// 0.994828895).
//
// Construction:
//   - The 93 measured DAC codes hold the calibrated V4 measurement
//     exactly.
//   - At the three confirmed bit-flip boundaries 1024, 2048, and 3072
//     the measured (post-step) value sits at the boundary code, and
//     the codes between the previous measurement and the boundary are
//     filled by log-linear interpolation to the lower-branch
//     projection (linearly extrapolated in log2(freq) from the prior
//     two measurements). The step lands between code B-1 and code B,
//     where bit-boundary INL physically belongs.
//   - Every other gap is plain log-linear interpolation in log2(freq)
//     between adjacent measurements.
//
// V4 step magnitudes at the boundaries (post-calibration):
//   DAC 1024: -4.64 cents
//   DAC 2048: +23.31 cents
//   DAC 3072: -4.48 cents
//
// Storage: 4096 * sizeof(double) = 32 KB.

